#!/bin/bash
cat <<-EOF | less -
i3 reference card 
===================================================

Basics
---------------------------------------------------
mod+enter             - open new terminal
mod+h                 - focus left
mod+j                 - focus down
mod+k                 - focus up
mod+l                 - focus right
mod+space             - toggle focus mode

Moving windows
---------------------------------------------------
mod+shift+h           - move window left
mod+shift+j           - move window down
mod+shift+k           - move window up
mod+shift+l           - move window right

Modifying windows
---------------------------------------------------
mod+f                 - toggle fullscreen
mod+s                 - split a window vertically
mod+v                 - split a window horizontally
mod+r                 - resize mode

Changing container layout
---------------------------------------------------
mod+e                 - toggle split
mod+s                 - stacked
mod+w                 - tabbed
mod+a                 - focus parent

Floating
---------------------------------------------------
mod+shift+space       - toggle floating
mod+mouse             - drag floating

Using workspaces
---------------------------------------------------
mod+tab               - next workspace
mod+shift+tab         - previous workspace
mod+0-9               - switch to another workspace
mod+shift+0-9         - move window to a workspace

Opening applications / Closing windows
---------------------------------------------------
mod+d                 - open app launcher
mod+c                 - open chrome
mod+q                 - kill focused window
mod+shift+q           - kill all windows

Restart / Exit
---------------------------------------------------
mod+shift+c           - reload config file
mod+shift+r           - restart i3 inplace
mod+shift+e           - exit i3

Misc
---------------------------------------------------
nmcli dev wifi                  - find wifi ap's
nmcli device wifi connect [ap]  - connect to ap
EOF
